<head><title>Internet Pinball Machine Database: Bally 'Hi-Fi'</title>
<META HTTP-EQUIV="imagetoolbar" CONTENT="no">
<meta name="keywords" content="IPD IPDB Internet Pinball Machine Database Game Bally Hi-Fi HiFi Bingo Machine Trap holes (25), Rollover buttons (2). 1 regular card and 2 smaller Super Cards. Bump-feature. A button on each side of the cabinet (where flipper buttons would be) allows the player to 'bump' the playfield up to ten times per game. This action jolts the playfield away from the player, allowing a playfield post to hit a rolling ball upfield. There is a delay feature on the tilt circuit to prevent tilting during a 'bump'.  Don Hooker ">
